Medic! We need a medic over here now.

177
00:38:28,467 --> 00:38:32,600
Hang on, mate. Hang on. Hang on.

178
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:37,467
We´re supposed to be training,
didn´t you know the rules?

179
00:38:37,667 --> 00:38:39,800
Jesus!

180
00:39:11,267 --> 00:39:14,333
You take a good look

181
00:39:14,533 --> 00:39:21,400
because that is what happens to tossers
who don´t pay attention.

182
00:39:23,467 --> 00:39:29,867
Now strip him. I said strip him!

183
00:40:18,267 --> 00:40:20,733
Stand aside.

184
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,200
Toss him over.

185
00:40:55,667 --> 00:41:01,067
<i>In no way am I condoning the appalling
events of yesterday.</i>

186
00:41:01,267 --> 00:41:08,267
<i>All I´m saying is that the stance
the UKand the US take internationally,</i>

187
00:41:08,467 --> 00:41:14,400
<i>it can be interpreted by certain groups
as provocation.</i>

188
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:17,000
<i>Can you elaborate on that?</i>

189
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:22,533
<i>Right, well, take Tyrgyztan,
where I was ambassador.</i>

190
00:41:22,733 --> 00:41:29,200
<i>Since ´99, the UKand the US
have invested over 50 billion dollars,</i>

191
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:39,067
<i>and at the same time 10,000 political prisoners
have disappeared under President Usman´s rule.</i>

192
00:41:39,267 --> 00:41:44,467
<i>Did you inform your government at the time
of suspected human rights abuse?</i>

193
00:41:44,667 --> 00:41:50,133
<i>Of course, but every cable
I sent to London, nothing.</i>

194
00:41:50,333 --> 00:41:55,533
<i>Deafening silence from the other end,
and that´s when I started to speak up.</i>

195
00:41:55,733 --> 00:42:02,200
<i>You´re saying the UKgovernment deliberately
ignored your allegations?</i>

196
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:07,733
<i>Not only that, they hauled me home,
slapped my wrists,</i>

197
00:42:07,933 --> 00:42:11,800
<i>and when that didn´t work,
they sacked me.</i>

198
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:20,333
<i>It´s this questionable support of corrupt regimes
that helps inflame the enemies of the West.</i>

199
00:42:20,533 --> 00:42:22,533
<i>Thank you, James.</i>

200
00:42:22,733 --> 00:42:31,133
<i>That was James Sinclair.
British Ambassador to Tyrgyztan, 1997 to 2001.</i>

201
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:35,800
<i>Now back to the news team for an update
on the terrorist attack.</i>

202
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:39,267
Well, you´re looking well.

203
